t, she was at peace. Prehaps that is why the pack of roaming wolves pasted her by, leaving her in peace. Prehaps that is why no gnolls appeared in the area, screaming for blood. Prehaps.....so many things hinge on the unknown. Soon would be the time to return to Neriak. To discover what had taken place last she left. To learn what ancient writtings hide within their harsh lines. But not at that moment. No, now was the time for watching the sun, the sun plumment into darkness... As Katrinity silently gazed out over the sea of grass, dark clouds rolled in with the wind from behind her. Drops of rain, few to begin, many in but a few moments, pounded into the earth, plastering grass and silver hair down. The tip of the sun flared one more time over the distant horizon, falling into darkness, as drops of water rolled down ebony skin, past ice-blue eyes, fresh mixing with salt to taste bitter-sweet upon shaded lips. <br>
